## 2. Version + deployment

### 2.1. PostgreSQL versions

Use **latest stable major** version (16, 17 как 2026). Each major — new features + perf improvements; obsolete versions reach EOL после 5 лет.

Major version updates **require careful planning** — extension compatibility, possible breaking changes. Plan annual major upgrade в release cycle.

### 2.2. Deployment options

| Option | Когда |
|---|---|
| **Managed service** (RDS / Cloud SQL / Azure DB / Supabase / Neon / Crunchy) | Default для production. Backups / monitoring / failover handled. Cost premium vs self-hosted |
| **Self-hosted on VM** | Cost-sensitive, full control. Operational overhead substantial — DBA expertise needed |
| **Self-hosted on Kubernetes** (CloudNativePG / Crunchy Postgres Operator / Zalando Patroni) | K8s shop с DBA expertise. Operator handles failover/backups |
| **Embedded для tests** (postgres testcontainers / pg_tmp) | Test environments — каждый test получает fresh PG instance |

**Recommend:** managed service unless cost / compliance / control reasons. Cloud-managed снимает operational toil.

### 2.3. Setup checklist для new instance

- [ ] PostgreSQL major version chosen (latest stable)
- [ ] Encryption at rest enabled (managed: usually default, verify)
- [ ] TLS enforced для connections (`sslmode=require` minimum, `verify-full` ideal)
- [ ] Backup configured (automated daily + WAL archive для PITR)
- [ ] Monitoring connected (Datadog / Cloud-native / Prometheus + postgres_exporter)
- [ ] `pg_stat_statements` extension installed (track query stats)
- [ ] Connection pool sized (см. § 8)
- [ ] Maintenance window scheduled (autovacuum tuning)

