## 3. Connection pooling

### 3.1. Driver-level vs external pooler

**Driver pool** (psycopg / pgx / node-postgres / etc) — стандарт для most apps:
- Connection cached в app process
- Per-app-instance pool
- 10-50 connections per app instance typical

**External pooler** (PgBouncer / Odyssey / pgcat) — когда:
- App instances × pool size > PostgreSQL max_connections (typically 100-200)
- Many short-lived connections (PHP / Lambda / serverless)
- Transaction-mode pooling extracts more throughput
- Multi-tenant routing

### 3.2. PgBouncer modes

| Mode | Behavior | Когда |
|---|---|---|
| **Session** | Connection assigned to client for session duration | Default; supports all PG features |
| **Transaction** | Connection released after each transaction | High throughput; **disables** session-bound features (LISTEN/NOTIFY, prepared statements, advisory locks) |
| **Statement** | Connection released after each statement | Extreme cases; many limitations |

**Most apps:** transaction mode + driver-level workarounds для prepared statements (либо disable, либо use unique statement names per pool worker).

### 3.3. Pool sizing rule

```
pool_size_per_app = ((cpu_cores * 2) + effective_spindle_count)
total_connections = pool_size_per_app * num_app_instances
```

Should NOT exceed `max_connections - reserved` (usually 100-200 - 20 reserved for admin / replication).

Если total > max — нужен PgBouncer.

