## 4. PostgreSQL data types — modern picks

### 4.1. Recommended types

| Use case | Type |
|---|---|
| Internal IDs | `bigserial` / `GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY` (PG 10+) |
| Public IDs | `uuid` с default `uuidv7()` (native в PG 17+) или extension `pg_uuidv7` для PG ≤ 16 (см. § 13); `gen_random_uuid()` для v4 |
| Money | `numeric(18,4)` |
| Text | `text` (no length penalty vs varchar) |
| Enum-like | `text` + CHECK constraint (avoid native ENUM type — миграции painful) |
| Timestamps | `timestamptz` (см. base.md § 5) |
| JSON | `jsonb` (binary, indexable; не `json`) |
| Booleans | `boolean` |
| IP addresses | `inet` (validates format) |
| URLs | `text` + CHECK |
| Geographic | PostGIS `geometry` / `geography` |

### 4.2. JSONB usage

См. base.md § 4.5 — JSONB для truly variable schema. PostgreSQL-specific:

```sql
-- GIN index для query paths
CREATE INDEX idx_events_payload_gin ON events USING GIN(payload jsonb_path_ops);

-- Query specific path
SELECT * FROM events WHERE payload @> '{"user": {"id": 123}}';
SELECT * FROM events WHERE payload->'user'->>'email' = 'x@y.com';
```

`jsonb_path_ops` index — для `@>` / `<@` containment queries (most common). `jsonb_ops` (default) — для broader query types.

### 4.3. Arrays

PostgreSQL supports arrays natively:

```sql
tags text[] NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
```

GIN index на `text[]` columns. Caveat — arrays violate 1NF, use sparingly (для simple tag lists OK, для structured data use separate table).

