## 5. Indexing strategy — PostgreSQL specifics

### 5.1. Index types

| Type | When |
|---|---|
| **B-tree** (default) | Equality + range queries |
| **Hash** | Equality only (PG 10+, mostly B-tree wins) |
| **GIN** | JSONB containment, array containment, full-text search |
| **GiST** | Geometric data (PostGIS), full-text (older), exclusion constraints |
| **BRIN** (block range) | Very large tables со natural data ordering (time-series). Compact, fast for range scans |
| **SP-GiST** | Specialized (phone numbers, IP ranges) |

### 5.2. Partial indexes

```sql
-- Index only active users
CREATE INDEX idx_users_email_active ON users(email) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;

-- Index only specific status
CREATE INDEX idx_orders_pending ON orders(created_at) WHERE status = 'pending';
```

Smaller indexes, faster queries для targeted use cases.

### 5.3. Expression indexes

```sql
-- Lowercase email lookup
CREATE INDEX idx_users_email_lower ON users(lower(email));

-- Then query uses index
SELECT * FROM users WHERE lower(email) = lower('Foo@Bar.com');
```

### 5.4. Multi-column index ordering

Column order matters: index `(a, b)` works для filters on `a` alone or `a AND b`, but NOT `b` alone.

Rule: **most selective column first**, OR **column that's always filtered first**.

### 5.5. Index maintenance

- `REINDEX CONCURRENTLY` (PG 12+) periodically для bloated indexes
- Monitor `pg_stat_user_indexes.idx_scan` — unused indexes wasted resources
- `pg_stat_user_tables` — find missing indexes (high `seq_scan` on large tables)

### 5.6. CONCURRENTLY для production

```sql
-- Не блокирует writes; longer но safe
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_users_created_at ON users(created_at);
DROP INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_old;
REINDEX INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_users_email;
```

Без `CONCURRENTLY` — locks table. Production rule: **всегда `CONCURRENTLY`** для index DDL.

