## 10. Point-in-time recovery (PITR)

См. base.md § 14 — RTO/RPO. PostgreSQL specifics:

### 10.1. Setup

```
archive_mode = on
archive_command = 'aws s3 cp %p s3://my-backups/wal/%f'
```

+ regular `pg_basebackup` (full backups).

### 10.2. Restore to point-in-time

```bash
# Restore base backup
tar xf base.tar -C /var/lib/postgresql/data

# Configure recovery
echo "restore_command = 'aws s3 cp s3://my-backups/wal/%f %p'" >> postgresql.conf
echo "recovery_target_time = '2026-05-24 14:30:00 UTC'" >> postgresql.conf
touch /var/lib/postgresql/data/recovery.signal

# Start postgres — replays WAL up to target time
pg_ctl start
```

Managed services (RDS / Cloud SQL) — UI for PITR within retention period.

### 10.3. Backup verification

- `pg_verify_backup` (PG 13+)
- Restore drill — restore to staging, run integrity checks
- Quarterly: full disaster recovery drill в alternate region

