## 11. Performance tuning

### 11.1. Critical settings (per server)

```
shared_buffers = 25% RAM        # OS page cache stays for rest
effective_cache_size = 75% RAM  # planner hint (not allocation)
work_mem = (RAM - shared_buffers) / max_connections / 4  # per-operation
maintenance_work_mem = 1 GB     # для VACUUM / CREATE INDEX
random_page_cost = 1.1          # SSD (default 4.0 for HDD)
```

### 11.2. Slow query log

```
log_min_duration_statement = 100ms
```

+ regular review через `pg_stat_statements`:

```sql
SELECT query, calls, total_exec_time, mean_exec_time, rows
FROM pg_stat_statements
ORDER BY total_exec_time DESC LIMIT 20;
```

### 11.3. EXPLAIN ANALYZE workflow

```sql
EXPLAIN (ANALYZE, BUFFERS, VERBOSE, FORMAT JSON)
SELECT ...;
```

Key signals:
- `Seq Scan` on large table → missing index
- `Sort` writing to disk → increase work_mem
- `Nested Loop` с large outer + non-indexed inner → algorithm choice issue
- `Hash Join` with «Batches: N» (N > 1) → spilling to disk

Tooling: PEV ([Postgres Explain Visualizer](https://explain.dalibo.com)), pganalyze, Datadog DBM.

### 11.4. Autovacuum tuning

Per-table tuning для high-update tables:

```sql
ALTER TABLE high_churn_table SET (
  autovacuum_vacuum_scale_factor = 0.01,   -- vacuum после 1% changes vs 20% default
  autovacuum_analyze_scale_factor = 0.005
);
```

Bloated tables (table size >> data) — autovacuum не keeping up. `pg_repack` для online table rebuild.

