## 12. Security baseline — PostgreSQL specifics

### 12.1. Authentication

- **Password** (`scram-sha-256` since PG 10) — minimum для new setups
- **Certificate** (client cert) — для service-to-service
- **IAM authentication** (AWS RDS / Cloud SQL) — integrates с cloud IAM
- **SSO** через third-party (Active Directory / OIDC)

`pg_hba.conf`:
```
hostssl all all 0.0.0.0/0 scram-sha-256
```

### 12.2. Role hierarchy

```sql
-- Service roles
CREATE ROLE app_reader;
CREATE ROLE app_writer INHERIT app_reader;
CREATE ROLE app_migrator;

-- Users belong to roles
CREATE USER my_app_user WITH PASSWORD '...';
GRANT app_writer TO my_app_user;
```

### 12.3. Audit logging — pgaudit

Extension `pgaudit` logs DDL / DML / role changes:

```
shared_preload_libraries = 'pgaudit'
pgaudit.log = 'ddl, role, write'
```

Logs to PostgreSQL log file (or syslog / journald). Forward to centralized logging.

### 12.4. Encryption — pgcrypto for app-level

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION pgcrypto;

-- Encrypt
INSERT INTO secrets (encrypted_value)
VALUES (pgp_sym_encrypt('plaintext', current_setting('app.encryption_key')));

-- Decrypt
SELECT pgp_sym_decrypt(encrypted_value::bytea, current_setting('app.encryption_key'))
FROM secrets;
```

`pgcrypto` — для column-level encryption когда selective fields require encryption. Не replacement для disk encryption (это at-rest layer).

### 12.5. SSL / TLS configuration

```
ssl = on
ssl_min_protocol_version = 'TLSv1.3'  -- modern; falls back если client supports only 1.2
ssl_cert_file = 'server.crt'
ssl_key_file = 'server.key'
```

Client (`psycopg`, `pgx`, etc):
```
sslmode=verify-full
sslrootcert=/path/to/ca.crt
```

`verify-full` validates server cert против CA — protects от MITM.

