## 14. MySQL / MariaDB notes

Где отличается от PostgreSQL:

### 14.1. Types

- No `text[]` arrays — workaround с JSON
- No native UUID type — store as `BINARY(16)` или `CHAR(36)`
- `JSON` type (since 5.7) — analogous to JSONB но different query syntax
- No `inet` — store as `VARCHAR(45)` (IPv6 max length)

### 14.2. Replication

- Master-slave (binlog-based) — replication different model from PG streaming
- GTID для consistent failover (replaces server log position)
- MariaDB MaxScale / ProxySQL — connection routing

### 14.3. Storage engines

- **InnoDB** (default since 5.5) — ACID, foreign keys
- MyISAM — **never use** for production (no transactions, no FK)

### 14.4. Encryption

- TDE (Transparent Data Encryption) — MySQL Enterprise / Percona
- MariaDB — built-in encryption at rest

### 14.5. When MySQL/MariaDB make sense

- Existing ecosystem / team expertise
- Simpler setup для very small projects
- WordPress / Magento / legacy systems

**For new modern projects:** PostgreSQL рекомендуется unless specific reason otherwise.

